On April 10, 2013, President Barack Obama issued a Sequestration Order for Fiscal Year 2014. This order was made in accordance with section 251A of the Balanced Budget and Emergency Deficit Control Act and mandated that on October 1, 2013, direct spending budgetary resources for fiscal year 2014 in each non-exempt budget account be reduced. The specific amount of reduction was calculated by the Office of Management and Budget and outlined in their report to Congress on April 10, 2013. The order emphasized that all sequestrations should adhere to the requirements of section 251A of the Act and the specifications of the Office of Management and Budget's report.